Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Redis connection fails

Check if Redis is running: sudo systemctl status redis-server
Restart Redis: sudo systemctl restart redis-server
Verify port 6379 is available: netstat -an | grep 6379
Issue: Rate limiting not working

Ensure Redis is running and accessible
Check Flask-Limiter configuration
Verify rate limit decorators are applied correctly
Issue: Logs not being written

Check file permissions in working directory
Verify logging configuration in code
Ensure log file path is correct
Issue: API returns 500 errors

Check application logs for stack traces
Verify all required modules are imported
Test individual functions separately
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated essential security practices for GenAI applications. You implemented authentication, rate limiting, input sanitization, and log analysis to protect against common attacks. These techniques form the foundation of secure GenAI workflows in production environments.

Key takeaways:

Always authenticate and authorize API requests
Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse
Sanitize inputs to detect prompt injection
Monitor logs continuously for attack patterns
Apply defense-in-depth security strategies
Continue practicing these security measures and stay updated on emerging GenAI threats and mitigation techniques.
